About me

I'm the marketing executive for you

I’m a seasoned conversion copywriter who transforms ideas into compelling narratives that drive action. With expertise in consumer psychology, I craft copy that captures attention and boosts sales. Let’s turn your vision into words that deliver real results.

Direction

I guide your brand’s voice, ensuring every message aligns with your vision and resonates with your audience.

Copywriting

I craft engaging, high-converting copy that drives action and connects with your customers.

Strategy

I develop tailored content strategies that align with your business objectives and ensure long-term success.

Why words matter

In today’s competitive landscape, your words are your first impression. Whether it’s on your website, in an email, or a product description, the right copy can turn visitors into customers. With professionally crafted copy, you can:

  • Boost Conversions: Persuasive, targeted language leads to more sales and engagement.
  • Build Trust: Clear, authentic messaging strengthens your brand’s credibility.
  • Save Time: A copywriter lets you focus on running your business while ensuring every word works hard for you.

Don’t let your message fall flat—let’s make your words count!

61SELECT bcl_posts.ID
FROM bcl_posts
INNER JOIN bcl_postmeta
ON ( bcl_posts.ID = bcl_postmeta.post_id )
WHERE 1=1
AND ( ( bcl_postmeta.meta_key = '_elementor_template_type'
AND bcl_postmeta.meta_value = 'landing-page' ) )
AND bcl_posts.post_type = 'e-landing-page'
AND ((bcl_posts.post_status <> 'trash'

82SELECT SQL_CALC_FOUND_ROWS bcl_posts.ID
FROM bcl_posts
INNER JOIN bcl_postmeta
ON ( bcl_posts.ID = bcl_postmeta.post_id )
INNER JOIN bcl_postmeta AS mt1
ON ( bcl_posts.ID = mt1.post_id )
WHERE 1=1
AND ( bcl_postmeta.meta_key = '_elementor_template_type'
AND ( ( mt1.meta_key = '_elementor_template_type'
AND mt1.meta_value = 'popup' ) ) )
AND bcl_posts.post_type = 'elementor_library'
AND ((bcl_posts.post_status <> 'trash'
AND bcl_posts.post_status <> 'auto-draft'))

132SELECT bcl_posts.*
FROM bcl_posts
INNER JOIN bcl_postmeta
ON ( bcl_posts.ID = bcl_postmeta.post_id )
INNER JOIN bcl_postmeta AS mt1
ON ( bcl_posts.ID = mt1.post_id )
WHERE 1=1
AND ( bcl_postmeta.meta_key = '_elementor_priority'
AND ( ( mt1.meta_key = '_elementor_location'
AND mt1.meta_value = 'elementor_head' ) ) )
AND bcl_posts.post_type = 'elementor_snippet'
AND ((bcl_posts.post_status = 'publish'))
GROUP BY bcl_posts.ID
ORDER BY bcl_postmeta.meta_value+0 ASC

145SELECT bcl_posts.*
FROM bcl_posts
INNER JOIN bcl_postmeta
ON ( bcl_posts.ID = bcl_postmeta.post_id )
INNER JOIN bcl_postmeta AS mt1
ON ( bcl_posts.ID = mt1.post_id )
WHERE 1=1
AND ( bcl_postmeta.meta_key = '_elementor_priority'
AND ( ( mt1.meta_key = '_elementor_location'
AND mt1.meta_value = 'elementor_body_start' ) ) )
AND bcl_posts.post_type = 'elementor_snippet'
AND ((bcl_posts.post_status = 'publish'))
GROUP BY bcl_posts.ID
ORDER BY bcl_postmeta.meta_value+0 ASC

Configuration

The following PHP constants can be defined in your wp-config.php file in order to control the behavior of Query Monitor:

QM_DB_EXPENSIVE
If an individual database query takes longer than this time to execute, it's considered "slow" and triggers a warning.
Default value: 0.05
QM_DISABLED
Disable Query Monitor entirely.
Default value: false
QM_DISABLE_ERROR_HANDLER
Disable the handling of PHP errors.
Default value: false
QM_ENABLE_CAPS_PANEL
Enable the Capability Checks panel.
Default value: false
QM_HIDE_CORE_ACTIONS
Hide WordPress core on the Hooks & Actions panel.
Default value: false
QM_HIDE_SELF
Hide Query Monitor itself from various panels. Set to false if you want to see how Query Monitor hooks into WordPress.
Default value: true
QM_NO_JQUERY
Don't specify jQuery as a dependency of Query Monitor. If jQuery isn't enqueued then Query Monitor will still operate, but with some reduced functionality.
Default value: false
QM_SHOW_ALL_HOOKS
In the Hooks & Actions panel, show every hook that has an action or filter attached (instead of every action hook that fired during the request).
Default value: false
QM_DB_SYMLINK
Allow the wp-content/db.php file symlink to be put into place during activation. Set to false to prevent the symlink creation.
Default value: true
